# Agent Harness Environment Architecture

This repo has two product surfaces:

1. Hosted demo surface using static fixtures.
2. Local developer surface that can run tasks, emit traces, and score runs.

Keep these boundaries:

- `apps/web` renders the hosted product demo. It should default to static data and never require live LLM calls.
- `packages/harness` owns TypeScript trace schema, policy definitions, tool contracts, and harness primitives.
- `packages/evals` owns deterministic and heuristic scoring code.
- `packages/reward` owns RL-lite policy routing and reward calculation.
- `services/runner` owns local task execution, sandboxing, command allow-listing, and trace emission.
- `tools/mcp_server.py` exposes local project data and eval tools to Cursor.
- `data` contains static fixtures used by the hosted demo.

When implementing a feature, prefer the smallest vertical slice that preserves this architecture.

Do not move live runner concerns into the hosted demo. Do not make the hosted demo depend on external APIs.
